                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1040">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/3–1546</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-15T14:00:00+07:00"
                            >March 15, 1946—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 21—1:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>494. Purpose of Embtel 330, February 20, 8 a.m. (Reurtel 401, March 5) was to
                    enable us to answer inquiry made by Josselyn at Shanghai in his despatch No. 61
                        [<hi rend="italic">21</hi>], February 9,<note n="17" xml:id="d1040fn17">Not
                        printed.</note> reconstruction of article 4 of 1943 extraterritoriality
                    treaty. Copy of Josselyn’s despatch has been forwarded to Dept by Shanghai. Copy
                    of our reply to Josselyn being sent by air mail.<note n="18" xml:id="d1040fn18">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
